properties.headline: Air Quality Alert issued January 30 at 2:10AM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
Strong northwest winds of 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 55 mph are
expected this afternoon. The winds will begin to subside late this
afternoon and early evening.

The Wyoming Air Quality Division recommends the elderly, young
children, and individuals with respiratory problems avoid excessive
physical exertion and minimize outdoor activities during this time.
Although these people are most susceptible to health impacts, the air
quality division also advises that everyone should avoid prolonged
exposure to the poor air quality conditions.

NWSheadline: BLOWING DUST HEALTH ALERT IN EFFECT FOR THE POWDER RIVER BASIN OF NORTHEASTERN WYOMING FROM 11 AM UNTIL 5 PM TODAY
